is_rhoai_2x()                       # Returns 0 if 2.x
```

### MaaS Configuration
```bash
get_maas_endpoint()                 # Sets MAAS_ENDPOINT, MAAS_NAMESPACE (version-aware)
```

### Dashboard URL
```bash
get_dashboard_url()                 # Returns URL (3.3+: data-science-gateway, else: rhods-dashboard)
```

### Feature Store Utilities
```bash
get_featurestore_labels()           # Required labels for version
check_featurestore_labels(ns, name) # Verify labels
fix_featurestore_labels(ns, name)   # Add missing labels
check_featurestore_registry(ns, name) # Verify restAPI setting
fix_featurestore_registry(ns, name) # Enable restAPI
diagnose_featurestore(ns, name)     # Full diagnostic with auto-fix option
```

### Model Serving CRD Detection
```bash
is_llmd_available()                 # Check if LLMInferenceService CRD exists
is_kserve_available()               # Check if InferenceService CRD exists
list_deployed_models([namespace])   # List all models (both CR types)
```

**RHOAI 3.3 CR Usage** (determined by runtime choice, not version):
- `LLMInferenceService` (v1alpha1) - ONLY for llm-d runtime (required for MaaS)
- `InferenceService` (v1beta1) - All other runtimes (vLLM, OpenVINO, Caikit-TGIS, NIM, etc.)

See `lib/functions/model-deployment.sh` for actual deployment logic.

### Info Display
```bash
print_rhoai_info()                  # Display version, dashboard URL, component status
```

